[]: New people vs. new world &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Quote Post by Ah Q &raquo; Wed Aug 18, 2021 5:53 pm I noticed a discrepancy between the English subtitles and English dub of 3.0+1.0. During the &quot;Neon Genesis&quot; scene, Shinji says the following in the English dub: I won't rewind time or revert the world. I'm just going to rewrite the world into one that doesn't have Evas. A world where new people can live.

[]: Re: New people vs. new world &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Quote Post by Raikyu &raquo; Wed Aug 18, 2021 6:10 pm I remember when the script leaked in March, and the translations at the time said &quot;new world&quot;.

[]: Re: New people vs. new world &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Quote Post by aboose &raquo; Wed Aug 18, 2021 7:59 pm Sure, I'll check it for you. 時間も世界も戻さない I won't turn back time or the world. ただ, エヴァがなくてもいい世界に書き換えるだけだ I will just rewrite the world to be okay without Evangelion 新しい人が生きていける世界に A new world where people can go on to live 世界の新たな創生 Rei: The creation of a new world ネオンジェネシス Rei: Neon Genesis. The reason the person originally mistranslated it is because in Japanese, the word order is different than English. The literal translation of this line: 新しい人が生きていける世界に &quot;New people can go on living in world to&quot; At first glance it can look like the modifier &quot;new&quot; is applied to &quot;people&quot;, but it's actually applied to &quot;world&quot; as you would use a comma in English: &quot;New, people can go on living in, world to&quot; This is highlighted by Ayanami's next line highlighting that it's the creation of a new world, not a new people.

