[]: Re: New people vs. new world &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Quote Post by NightComesOn &raquo; Fri Aug 20, 2021 9:41 am The biggest revelation for me here is that Shinji isn't just creating a &quot;world that doesn't have Evas.&quot; He's creating a world that will be &quot;okay without Evangelion.&quot; That seems to me like a major change of meaning. He's not getting rid of Evas; he's getting rid of the NEED for Evas. In a diegetic sense I suppose that means a world without the FAR and the seeds and the angels--where Eva is necessary. In a meta sense, I think it means &quot;You can move on from Evangelion now. We as a world have moved beyond the need for Evangelion. Time to go up the stairs into the real world.&quot;

